<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[140,1107,1609,1672]" lastBlockId="5.[140,1108,166,475]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[140,267,1609,1635]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Strecker" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[461,556,1610,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudohemihyalea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ambigua">
<emphasis box="[461,556,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">ambigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group can be immediately recognized by the simple, striate forewing pattern (
<figureCitation box="[565,669,1645,1672]" captionStart="Figures 1-5. 1" captionStartId="2.[140,222,1336,1358]" captionTargetBox="[155,1101,181,1299]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[140,1108,165,1316]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1-5. 1a. P. ambigua male (Santa Cruz Co., AZ, USA). 1b. P. ambigua female (Cochise Co., AZ, USA). 2a. P. syracosia male (Zacapa Dpto., Guatemala). 2b. P. syracosia female (Chiapas, Mexico). 3a. P. fallaciosa male (Chiapas, Mexico). 3b. P. fallaciosa female (Zacapa Dpto., Guatemala). 4a. P. sonorosa male paratype (Sonora, Mexico). 4b. P. sonorosa female paratype (Sonora, Mexico). 5. P. potosi male holotype (Nuevo Leon, Mexico)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3810645" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3810645/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Figs. 1-5</figureCitation>
). Internally, the male uncus in dorsal profile is characteristically shaped like a bicycle saddle (Figs. 11-15), with the apex slightly down-turned, pointed and beak-like (Fig. 6). The posterior portion of the uncus consists of two heavily setose, globose or slightly flattened lobes (Fig. 6). The male valve is relatively simple and bipartite (tripartite in most 
<taxonomicName box="[839,929,273,299]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Amastus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[839,929,273,299]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Amastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a few 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Toulgoet" baseAuthorityYear="1994" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudohemihyalea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Pseudohemihyalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), with the apical 1/3 to ¼ divided into costal and saccullar processes (figs. 6-10). The transtilla is low, hump-like and finely scobinate (coarsely spinose or scobinate in most other 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Toulgoet" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[428,623,378,404]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudohemihyalea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[428,623,378,404]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Pseudohemihyalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, long, prong-like and variously scobinate in 
<taxonomicName box="[171,261,413,439]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Amastus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[171,261,413,439]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Amastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Female genitalia are relatively simple across the whole 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
Pseudohemihylaea- 
<taxonomicName box="[140,230,449,475]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Amastus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Amastus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
group, and no characters were found that distinguish the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Strecker" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[875,970,448,474]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudohemihyalea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ambigua">
<emphasis box="[875,970,448,474]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">ambigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group from
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3810649" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3810649" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3810649/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" startId="5.[140,222,1590,1612]" targetBox="[153,1097,560,1566]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[140,1108,1590,1676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[140,300,1590,1612]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Figures 6-1 0. 6</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Strecker" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[311,414,1590,1612]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudohemihyalea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ambigua">
<emphasis box="[311,324,1591,1612]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[336,414,1590,1611]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">ambigua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, right lateral view of male genital capsule, aedeagus removed. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[978,991,1590,1612]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">7</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[1002,1102,1591,1612]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudohemihyalea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syracosia">
<emphasis box="[1002,1015,1591,1612]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1027,1102,1591,1612]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">syracosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, lateral view of right valve. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[389,402,1622,1644]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">8</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Toulgoet" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[416,523,1622,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudohemihyalea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallaciosa">
<emphasis box="[416,429,1623,1644]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">P</emphasis>
